        {
          "id": "sec17",
          "type": "section",
          "number": "17",
          "title": "Commission’s prior approval required for certain changes.",
          "text": "",
          "level": 2,
          "references": [],
          "children": [
            {
              "id": "sec17:p1",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "number": "(1)",
              "title": "",
              "text": "A registrant who is desirous of making a change referred to in subsection (2), shall, as soon as practicable, but no less than twenty-eight days before the intended implementation of the proposed change — (a) apply in writing to the Commission for approval of the proposed change; and (b) pay the fee as prescribed by the Commission.",
              "level": 3,
              "references": [
                {
                  "target": "sec17:p2",
                  "text": "subsection (2)",
                  "type": "internal"
                }
              ],
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "id": "sec17:p2",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "number": "(2)",
              "title": "",
              "text": "For the purposes of subsection (1), the changes for which a registrant shall seek approval include — (a) a material change or expansion of the registrant’s scope of activities; (b) the merger, acquisition or sale of all or a substantial part of its assets to another entity; (c) the issue, transfer or other disposal of its shares; (d) the appointment of a new — (i) director; (ii) officer; (iii) chief executive officer; (iv) compliance officer; (v) money laundering reporting officer; (e) a change of its shareholders or beneficial owners; (f) a change or modification of its trading name; or (g) the appointment of an auditor.",
              "level": 3,
              "references": [
                {
                  "target": "sec17:p1",
                  "text": "subsection (1)",
                  "type": "internal"
                }
              ],
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "id": "sec17:p3",
              "type": "paragraph",
              "number": "(3)",
              "title": "",
              "text": "Notwithstanding subsection (1), where the holder of a post referred to in subsection (2)(d) or (g) ceases to hold that post, the registrant shall — (a) immediately notify the Commission of the vacancy by submitting Form 7 as set out in the First Schedule to the Commission; (b) apply for the approval of the new holder of the post within fourteen days of giving notice of the vacancy.",
              "level": 3,
              "references": [
